#Text=STRONG BEER AND PORTER FOR SALE, / WARE HAM, DORSET.

#Text=GREEN, On the Premises, without the least reservation, on Saturday, the 15th day of August, 1835, About 14,400 gallons of genuine STRONG BEER and PORTER, saved from the cahu mitous Fire at Mr Samuel Townsend’s Brewery, Ware ham.
